etupEclipseproject-Gettingstarted\">Getting started</a></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-GettingthelatestEclipseversion\">Getting the latest Eclipse version</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipse\">Starting Eclipse</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Workspaces\">Workspaces</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.4\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-TellingEclipsewhatworkspacetouse.\">Telling Eclipse what workspace to use.</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.5\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipseusingqrsh\">Starting Eclipse using qrsh</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Eclipseprojects\">Eclipse projects</a></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectusingCmake\">Creating Eclipse project using Cmake</a></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.1.1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingprojectfilesusingCMake\">Creating project files using CMake</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.1.2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-ImportingaprojectfilesgeneratewithCMakeintoEclipse\">Importing a project files generate with CMake into Eclipse</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectfileswithoutusingCMake\">Creating Eclipse project files without using CMake</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-MakingEclipsecodeanalyzer/editortorecognizeC++11additions(auto,shared_ptr,etc.)\">Making Eclipse code analyzer / editor to recognize C++11 additions (auto, shared_ptr, etc.)</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"4\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupbuildconfiguration\">Setting up build configuration</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"5\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupdebug(orrun)configuration)\">Setting up debug (or run) configuration)</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"6\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Excludetheunnecessaryfiles(tospeedupindexingandavoidunresolvedmethods)\">Exclude the unnecessary files (to speedup indexing and avoid unresolved methods)</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"7\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CodingStyleFile\">Coding Style File</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Gettingstarted\">Getting started</h1>\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-GettingthelatestEclipseversion\">Getting the latest Eclipse version</h2>\r\nThe recommended version is Eclipse Neon:\r\n<pre>get_env java18\r\nget_env eclipse_neon_4_6_3_RC2_cpp</pre>\r\nEclipse Oxygen is also available, but functionality has not been verified yet.\r\nTo get a list of available eclipse versions:\r\n<pre>get_env blabla | grep -i eclipse</pre>\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipse\">Starting Eclipse</h2>\r\nEclipse is started by the command\r\n<pre>eclipse</pre>\r\nBut the preferred way to start are in the following sections.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Workspaces\">Workspaces</h2>\r\nEclipse need to open a <em>workspace</em> when starting.\r\n\r\nA <em>workspace</em> is a directory managed by eclipse.\r\n\r\nAs default it is called <strong>workspace</strong> and located in the home directory.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-TellingEclipsewhatworkspacetouse.\">Telling Eclipse what workspace to use.</h2>\r\nIt is recommended to have the workspace separated from the git clone, but parallel to it.\r\n\r\nSo if the git clone of all-wiser is in <strong>/gridwrk1/GridWork/MyUsername/MyWiserStuff/all-wiser</strong>, the workspace to use is <strong>/gridwrk1/GridWork/MyUsername/MyWiserStuff/all-wiser/workspace</strong>.\r\n\r\nTo start eclipse with that workspace do\r\n<pre>cd /gridwrk1/GridWork/MyUsername/MyWiserStuff/all-wiser\r\neclipse -data workspace</pre>\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipseusingqrsh\">Starting Eclipse using qrsh</h2>\r\nEclipse should not be started directly on the machine hosting the vnc server, but on one of the grid execution hosts, using <em>qrsh</em>:\r\n\r\nThe simple version:\r\n<pre>qrsh -V -cwd -q nsnel6_i.q -m n \'eclipse -data workspace\'</pre>\r\nThere might be a need to allocate more memory:\r\n<pre>qrsh -V -cwd  -q nsnel6_i.q -l grid_vmem=10G -l h_stack=2G  \'eclipse -vmargs -Xmx2048m -Xms2048m -XX:MaxPermSize=2048m\'</pre>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Eclipseprojects\">Eclipse projects</h1>\r\nA project is the way to tell Eclipse what source code you want to interact with (edit, compile, debug etc.).\r\n\r\nProjects can be created manually, or the relevant files can be created by by CMake. Using CMake is a lot easier.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectusingCmake\">Creating Eclipse project using Cmake</h2>\r\n<h3 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingprojectfilesusingCMake\">Creating project files using CMake</h3>\r\nThe option -G to Cmake can be used to tell CMake what generators to use.\r\n\r\nThe default setup in FREx configuration is to generate Makefiles, some are using Ninja build files instead.\r\n\r\nTo tell CMake to also generate Eclipse project files use CMake option <strong><em>-G \"Eclipse CDT4 - Unix Makefiles\"</em></strong>, or for Ninja <strong><em>-G \"Eclipse CDT4 - Ninja\"</em></strong>\r\n\r\nThis has to be done in the build directory, e.g. build.Debug or build.Release:\r\n<pre>cd all-wiser-sims/freac/build.Debug</pre>\r\n<pre>../../common/bin/call_cmake.sh -G \"Eclipse CDT4 - Unix Makefiles\"</pre>\r\nIt will not destroy existing build information, so can be done in build directories that has previously been configured with CMake (directly or using bootstrap.sh of call_cmake.sh).\r\n\r\nThat will generate two files, <em><strong>.cproject</strong></em> and <em><strong>.project</strong></em>, that can be read by eclipse and contain all relevant information on how to build the project.\r\n<h3 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-ImportingaprojectfilesgeneratewithCMakeintoEclipse\">Importing a project files generate with CMake into Eclipse</h3>\r\nStart eclipse.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Chose menu item \"File → Import ...\"</li>\r\n 	<li>Chose \"General → Existing Projects into Workspace\" and \"Next &gt;\"</li>\r\n 	<li>In \"Select root directory\", use \"Browse\" to navigate to the build directory where you ran CMake with -G, and press OK. <strong>Important</strong>: choose the directory, not a file in the directory.</li>\r\n 	<li>In \"Projects:\" there should now be a project listed, e.g. something like \"<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"mailto:freac-Debug@build.Debug\" rel=\"nofollow\">freac-Debug@build.Debug</a> (/gridwrk2/GridWork ....)\".</li>\r\n 	<li>\"Finish\"</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIn \"Project Explorer\" the project will now be listed.\r\n\r\nIn the bottom of the screen you see \"C/C++ Indexer\" running.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectfileswithoutusingCMake\">Creating Eclipse project files without using CMake</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>File -&gt; New -&gt; Makefile Project with Existing Code</li>\r\n 	<li>Give project name, e.g., ‘all-wiser-sims’.</li>\r\n 	<li>Give location of your local copy of all-wiser-sims.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select ‘Linux GCC’ from ‘Toolchain for Indexer Settings’</li>\r\n 	<li>Click Finish (This can take a long time)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-MakingEclipsecodeanalyzer/editortorecognizeC++11additions(auto,shared_ptr,etc.)\">Making Eclipse code analyzer / editor to recognize C++11 additions (auto, shared_ptr, etc.)</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Create a project (next item) and select it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Project -&gt; Properties -&gt; C/C++ General -&gt; Preprocessor Include Paths, Macros etc.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Providers tab, select ‘CDT GCC Built-in Compiler Settings’ and click blue ‘Workspace Settings’ link\r\n<em>Eclipse NEON</em>: link do not exist anymore, go to step (5) directly.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Discovery tab, select again ‘CDT GCC Built-in Compiler Settings’.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add flag ‘-std=c++0x’ to ‘Command to get compiler specs’.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click OK (twice)</li>\r\n 	<li>Re-run indexer (Right-click you project and select ‘Index -&gt; Rebuild’ )</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupbuildconfiguration\">Setting up build configuration</h1>\r\n<strong>This is example for setting up debug configuration for wenla. Release config and other simulators goes similar way\r\nIt is also assumed that your build is already configured (e.g. build.Relese/Debug folders are created and ../../common/bin/bootstrap.sh has been executed in it). </strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Select newly created ‘all-wiser-sims’ project (by clicking it active).</li>\r\n 	<li>Project -&gt; Properties -&gt; C++ Build</li>\r\n 	<li>In Builder Settings tab, set build directory as: ${<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://workspace_loc/all-wiser-sims/wenla/build.Debug\" rel=\"nofollow\">workspace_loc:/all-wiser-sims/wenla/build.Debug</a>}</li>\r\n 	<li>In Behavior tab, Change value of ‘Build (Incremental build)’ to ‘–j20’</li>\r\n 	<li>Click OK</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYou can add several configurations: Project -&gt; Build Configuration -&gt; Manage…\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupdebug(orrun)configuration)\">Setting up debug (or run) configuration)</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Compile once in order to get binary available (Project -&gt; Build All; or small hammer on toolbar; or Ctrl+b)</li>\r\n 	<li>Run -&gt; Debug configurations… (or Run -&gt; Run Configuartions…)</li>\r\n 	<li>Select ‘C/C++ Application’ and press ‘New’ button above ‘type filter text’ –box</li>\r\n 	<li>In Main tab, give name of or browse the binary you want to be debugged (or run), e.g, ‘/proj/wiser-wa/username/all-wiser-sims/wenla/WENLA.Linux-2.6-x86_64-Debug’</li>\r\n 	<li>In Arguments tab, Select working directory to be the sims configuration directory from which you want to take the parameter configuration for the debug run, e.g., ‘${workspace_loc:all-wiser-sims/wenla/sims/Scenario1}’</li>\r\n 	<li>In Debugger tab, un-check ‘Stop start up at: main’ if you don’t want to debugger stop in main beginning of each run.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click Apply and Close or Debug</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Excludetheunnecessaryfiles(tospeedupindexingandavoidunresolvedmethods)\">Exclude the unnecessary files (to speedup indexing and avoid unresolved methods)</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Select project name</li>\r\n 	<li>Go to Project-&gt;Properties-&gt;Resources-&gt;Resource Filters</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the following filters</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Exclude all, Apply to Folders (also check “all children (recursive)”)</li>\r\n 	<li>Separately create filters for File and Folder Attribute “obsolete”, “code_for_later_use”, “3rd_party”.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CodingStyleFile\">Coding Style File</h1>\r\nCode highlighting and indenting file can be found in the repository:\r\n\r\nall-wiser-sims/common/style/eclipse/Eclipse_style.xml\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Window -&gt; Preferences -&gt; C/C++ -&gt; Code style -&gt; Formatter</li>\r\n 	<li>Import</li>\r\n 	<li>Select all-wiser-sims/common/style/eclipse/Eclipse_style.xml</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','HOW-TO setup Eclipse project','','draft','open','open','','','','','2018-10-18 08:59:52','2018-10-18 08:59:52','',0,'http://45.77.202.181/?p=179',0,'post','',0),(180,1,'2018-10-18 08:59:52','2018-10-18 08:59:52','<div id=\"main-header\" class=\"\">\r\n<div id=\"title-heading\" class=\"pagetitle with-breadcrumbs\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"content\" class=\"page view\">\r\n<div id=\"page-metadata-end\" class=\"assistive\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"main-content\" class=\"wiki-content\">\r\n\r\nThis page describes various aspects of how to use<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.eclipse.org/cdt/\" rel=\"nofollow\"> Eclipse CDT</a> for development of all-wiser-sim code. <strong>This page is being updated, currently not complete or correct.</strong>\r\n<div class=\"toc-macro client-side-toc-macro  conf-macro output-block hidden-outline\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-headerelements=\"H1,H2,H3,H4,H5,H6,H7\" data-macro-name=\"toc\">\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Gettingstarted\">Getting started</a></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-GettingthelatestEclipseversion\">Getting the latest Eclipse version</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipse\">Starting Eclipse</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Workspaces\">Workspaces</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.4\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-TellingEclipsewhatworkspacetouse.\">Telling Eclipse what workspace to use.</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"1.5\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipseusingqrsh\">Starting Eclipse using qrsh</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Eclipseprojects\">Eclipse projects</a></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectusingCmake\">Creating Eclipse project using Cmake</a></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.1.1\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingprojectfilesusingCMake\">Creating project files using CMake</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.1.2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-ImportingaprojectfilesgeneratewithCMakeintoEclipse\">Importing a project files generate with CMake into Eclipse</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"2.2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectfileswithoutusingCMake\">Creating Eclipse project files without using CMake</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-MakingEclipsecodeanalyzer/editortorecognizeC++11additions(auto,shared_ptr,etc.)\">Making Eclipse code analyzer / editor to recognize C++11 additions (auto, shared_ptr, etc.)</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"4\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupbuildconfiguration\">Setting up build configuration</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"5\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupdebug(orrun)configuration)\">Setting up debug (or run) configuration)</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"6\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Excludetheunnecessaryfiles(tospeedupindexingandavoidunresolvedmethods)\">Exclude the unnecessary files (to speedup indexing and avoid unresolved methods)</a></span></li>\r\n 	<li><span class=\"toc-item-body\" data-outline=\"7\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/display/wiser2015/HOW-TO+setup+Eclipse+project#HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CodingStyleFile\">Coding Style File</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Gettingstarted\">Getting started</h1>\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-GettingthelatestEclipseversion\">Getting the latest Eclipse version</h2>\r\nThe recommended version is Eclipse Neon:\r\n<pre>get_env java18\r\nget_env eclipse_neon_4_6_3_RC2_cpp</pre>\r\nEclipse Oxygen is also available, but functionality has not been verified yet.\r\nTo get a list of available eclipse versions:\r\n<pre>get_env blabla | grep -i eclipse</pre>\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipse\">Starting Eclipse</h2>\r\nEclipse is started by the command\r\n<pre>eclipse</pre>\r\nBut the preferred way to start are in the following sections.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Workspaces\">Workspaces</h2>\r\nEclipse need to open a <em>workspace</em> when starting.\r\n\r\nA <em>workspace</em> is a directory managed by eclipse.\r\n\r\nAs default it is called <strong>workspace</strong> and located in the home directory.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-TellingEclipsewhatworkspacetouse.\">Telling Eclipse what workspace to use.</h2>\r\nIt is recommended to have the workspace separated from the git clone, but parallel to it.\r\n\r\nSo if the git clone of all-wiser is in <strong>/gridwrk1/GridWork/MyUsername/MyWiserStuff/all-wiser</strong>, the workspace to use is <strong>/gridwrk1/GridWork/MyUsername/MyWiserStuff/all-wiser/workspace</strong>.\r\n\r\nTo start eclipse with that workspace do\r\n<pre>cd /gridwrk1/GridWork/MyUsername/MyWiserStuff/all-wiser\r\neclipse -data workspace</pre>\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-StartingEclipseusingqrsh\">Starting Eclipse using qrsh</h2>\r\nEclipse should not be started directly on the machine hosting the vnc server, but on one of the grid execution hosts, using <em>qrsh</em>:\r\n\r\nThe simple version:\r\n<pre>qrsh -V -cwd -q nsnel6_i.q -m n \'eclipse -data workspace\'</pre>\r\nThere might be a need to allocate more memory:\r\n<pre>qrsh -V -cwd  -q nsnel6_i.q -l grid_vmem=10G -l h_stack=2G  \'eclipse -vmargs -Xmx2048m -Xms2048m -XX:MaxPermSize=2048m\'</pre>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Eclipseprojects\">Eclipse projects</h1>\r\nA project is the way to tell Eclipse what source code you want to interact with (edit, compile, debug etc.).\r\n\r\nProjects can be created manually, or the relevant files can be created by by CMake. Using CMake is a lot easier.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectusingCmake\">Creating Eclipse project using Cmake</h2>\r\n<h3 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingprojectfilesusingCMake\">Creating project files using CMake</h3>\r\nThe option -G to Cmake can be used to tell CMake what generators to use.\r\n\r\nThe default setup in FREx configuration is to generate Makefiles, some are using Ninja build files instead.\r\n\r\nTo tell CMake to also generate Eclipse project files use CMake option <strong><em>-G \"Eclipse CDT4 - Unix Makefiles\"</em></strong>, or for Ninja <strong><em>-G \"Eclipse CDT4 - Ninja\"</em></strong>\r\n\r\nThis has to be done in the build directory, e.g. build.Debug or build.Release:\r\n<pre>cd all-wiser-sims/freac/build.Debug</pre>\r\n<pre>../../common/bin/call_cmake.sh -G \"Eclipse CDT4 - Unix Makefiles\"</pre>\r\nIt will not destroy existing build information, so can be done in build directories that has previously been configured with CMake (directly or using bootstrap.sh of call_cmake.sh).\r\n\r\nThat will generate two files, <em><strong>.cproject</strong></em> and <em><strong>.project</strong></em>, that can be read by eclipse and contain all relevant information on how to build the project.\r\n<h3 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-ImportingaprojectfilesgeneratewithCMakeintoEclipse\">Importing a project files generate with CMake into Eclipse</h3>\r\nStart eclipse.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Chose menu item \"File → Import ...\"</li>\r\n 	<li>Chose \"General → Existing Projects into Workspace\" and \"Next &gt;\"</li>\r\n 	<li>In \"Select root directory\", use \"Browse\" to navigate to the build directory where you ran CMake with -G, and press OK. <strong>Important</strong>: choose the directory, not a file in the directory.</li>\r\n 	<li>In \"Projects:\" there should now be a project listed, e.g. something like \"<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"mailto:freac-Debug@build.Debug\" rel=\"nofollow\">freac-Debug@build.Debug</a> (/gridwrk2/GridWork ....)\".</li>\r\n 	<li>\"Finish\"</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIn \"Project Explorer\" the project will now be listed.\r\n\r\nIn the bottom of the screen you see \"C/C++ Indexer\" running.\r\n<h2 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CreatingEclipseprojectfileswithoutusingCMake\">Creating Eclipse project files without using CMake</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>File -&gt; New -&gt; Makefile Project with Existing Code</li>\r\n 	<li>Give project name, e.g., ‘all-wiser-sims’.</li>\r\n 	<li>Give location of your local copy of all-wiser-sims.</li>\r\n 	<li>Select ‘Linux GCC’ from ‘Toolchain for Indexer Settings’</li>\r\n 	<li>Click Finish (This can take a long time)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-MakingEclipsecodeanalyzer/editortorecognizeC++11additions(auto,shared_ptr,etc.)\">Making Eclipse code analyzer / editor to recognize C++11 additions (auto, shared_ptr, etc.)</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Create a project (next item) and select it.</li>\r\n 	<li>Project -&gt; Properties -&gt; C/C++ General -&gt; Preprocessor Include Paths, Macros etc.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Providers tab, select ‘CDT GCC Built-in Compiler Settings’ and click blue ‘Workspace Settings’ link\r\n<em>Eclipse NEON</em>: link do not exist anymore, go to step (5) directly.</li>\r\n 	<li>In Discovery tab, select again ‘CDT GCC Built-in Compiler Settings’.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add flag ‘-std=c++0x’ to ‘Command to get compiler specs’.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click OK (twice)</li>\r\n 	<li>Re-run indexer (Right-click you project and select ‘Index -&gt; Rebuild’ )</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupbuildconfiguration\">Setting up build configuration</h1>\r\n<strong>This is example for setting up debug configuration for wenla. Release config and other simulators goes similar way\r\nIt is also assumed that your build is already configured (e.g. build.Relese/Debug folders are created and ../../common/bin/bootstrap.sh has been executed in it). </strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Select newly created ‘all-wiser-sims’ project (by clicking it active).</li>\r\n 	<li>Project -&gt; Properties -&gt; C++ Build</li>\r\n 	<li>In Builder Settings tab, set build directory as: ${<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://workspace_loc/all-wiser-sims/wenla/build.Debug\" rel=\"nofollow\">workspace_loc:/all-wiser-sims/wenla/build.Debug</a>}</li>\r\n 	<li>In Behavior tab, Change value of ‘Build (Incremental build)’ to ‘–j20’</li>\r\n 	<li>Click OK</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nYou can add several configurations: Project -&gt; Build Configuration -&gt; Manage…\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Settingupdebug(orrun)configuration)\">Setting up debug (or run) configuration)</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Compile once in order to get binary available (Project -&gt; Build All; or small hammer on toolbar; or Ctrl+b)</li>\r\n 	<li>Run -&gt; Debug configurations… (or Run -&gt; Run Configuartions…)</li>\r\n 	<li>Select ‘C/C++ Application’ and press ‘New’ button above ‘type filter text’ –box</li>\r\n 	<li>In Main tab, give name of or browse the binary you want to be debugged (or run), e.g, ‘/proj/wiser-wa/username/all-wiser-sims/wenla/WENLA.Linux-2.6-x86_64-Debug’</li>\r\n 	<li>In Arguments tab, Select working directory to be the sims configuration directory from which you want to take the parameter configuration for the debug run, e.g., ‘${workspace_loc:all-wiser-sims/wenla/sims/Scenario1}’</li>\r\n 	<li>In Debugger tab, un-check ‘Stop start up at: main’ if you don’t want to debugger stop in main beginning of each run.</li>\r\n 	<li>Click Apply and Close or Debug</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-Excludetheunnecessaryfiles(tospeedupindexingandavoidunresolvedmethods)\">Exclude the unnecessary files (to speedup indexing and avoid unresolved methods)</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Select project name</li>\r\n 	<li>Go to Project-&gt;Properties-&gt;Resources-&gt;Resource Filters</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the following filters</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Exclude all, Apply to Folders (also check “all children (recursive)”)</li>\r\n 	<li>Separately create filters for File and Folder Attribute “obsolete”, “code_for_later_use”, “3rd_party”.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1 id=\"HOW-TOsetupEclipseproject-CodingStyleFile\">Coding Style File</h1>\r\nCode highlighting and indenting file can be found in the repository:\r\n\r\nall-wiser-sims/common/style/eclipse/Eclipse_style.xml\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Window -&gt; Preferences -&gt; C/C++ -&gt; Code style -&gt; Formatter</li>\r\n 	<li>Import</li>\r\n 	<li>Select all-wiser-sims/common/style/eclipse/Eclipse_style.xml</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','HOW-TO setup Eclipse project','','inherit','closed','closed','','179-revision-v1','','','2018-10-18 08:59:52','2018-10-18 08:59:52','',179,'http://45.77.202.181/?p=180',0,'revision','',0),(181,1,'2019-04-03 03:41:10','2019-04-03 03:41:10','<h2 id=\"Howtoinstallsshfs-Step-by-stepguide\">Step-by-step guide</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Download the software from link <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://storage.googleapis.com/google-code-archive-downloads/v2/code.google.com/win-sshfs/win-sshfs-0.0.1.5-setup.exe\" rel=\"nofollow\">win-sshfs-0.0.1.5-setup.exe</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Click on \"Save File\"</li>\r\n 	<li>At the end of download, launch the installation program\r\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/download/attachments/495111419/image2017-4-4%208%3A45%3A51.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1491289289000&amp;api=v2\" height=\"250\" data-image-src=\"/download/attachments/495111419/image2017-4-4%208%3A45%3A51.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1491289289000&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"495111237\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2017-4-4 8:45:51.png\" data-base-url=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"495111419\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"3\" /></span></li>\r\n 	<li>Click \"Next\"\r\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" src=\"https://confluence.int.net.nokia.com/download/attachments/495111419/image2017-4-4%208%3A46%3A47.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1491289289000&amp;api=v2\" height=\"250\" data-image-src=\"/download/attachments/495111419/image2017-4-4%208%3A46%3A47.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1491289289000&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\